    English:
      'No more in secret drink, and then deny thy hidden fraud;<br />What in thy mind lies hid shall soon be known abroad',
    EnglishMeaning:
      "Let (the drunkard) give up saying 'I have never drunk'; (for) the moment (he drinks) he will simply betray his former attempt to conceal",
    Transliteration:
      'Kaliththariyen Enpadhu  Kaivituka  Nenjaththu<br />Oliththadhooum  Aange  Mikum',
